---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
import Section from '@/components/Section.astro';

const title = 'BibleWise - Privacy Policy';
const description = 'Privacy Policy for BibleWise - Bible Quiz & Trivia App';
---

<Base head={{ title, description }}>
	<Section>
		<article class="prose prose-gray dark:prose-invert max-w-4xl mx-auto">
			<h1>Privacy Policy for BibleWise</h1>
			<p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
				Last updated: February 8, 2026
			</p>

			<h2>Overview</h2>
			<p>
				BibleWise ("we", "our", or "the app") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our Bible quiz and trivia application.
			</p>

			<h2>Information We Collect</h2>
			<p>
				BibleWise is designed with privacy in mind. We collect minimal information necessary to provide our services:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>We don't require personal information like your name or email</li>
				<li>We don't access your contacts or photos</li>
				<li>We don't track your location</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Game Progress and User Data</h2>
			<p>
				To provide quiz and progress tracking features, we store the following locally on your device:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Level completion and star ratings</li>
				<li>Daily challenge streaks and history</li>
				<li>Timed mode best scores</li>
				<li>Hint balance</li>
				<li>Unlocked question packs</li>
				<li>Your preferences and settings</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				This data is stored locally on your device and is not transmitted to our servers.
			</p>

			<h2>Analytics and Crash Reporting</h2>
			<p>
				To improve the app experience, we use the following services:
			</p>

			<h3>Firebase Analytics</h3>
			<p>
				We use Firebase Analytics to understand general app usage patterns. This includes:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Feature usage statistics (anonymized)</li>
				<li>Game mode completion rates</li>
				<li>App launch frequency</li>
				<li>Device type and OS version</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				This data is anonymized and aggregated. We cannot identify individual users from this information.
			</p>

			<h3>Firebase Crashlytics</h3>
			<p>
				We use Firebase Crashlytics to identify and fix app crashes. When the app crashes, it may send:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Device model and OS version</li>
				<li>App version</li>
				<li>Crash stack traces</li>
				<li>Anonymous installation UUID</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>In-App Purchases</h2>
			<p>
				BibleWise offers hint packs and question packs through in-app purchases. Purchase processing is handled by:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Apple App Store</strong> for all transactions</li>
				<li><strong>RevenueCat</strong> for purchase management</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				We don't store payment information. All transactions are processed securely by Apple and RevenueCat.
			</p>

			<h2>Notifications</h2>
			<p>
				BibleWise may send local notifications to remind you about daily challenges and streaks. These notifications are scheduled locally on your device and do not involve any external servers. You can disable notifications at any time in your device settings.
			</p>

			<h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
			<p>
				BibleWise uses the following third-party services:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Firebase</a> - Analytics and crash reporting</li>
				<li><a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">RevenueCat</a> - Purchase management</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
			<p>
				BibleWise is suitable for all ages. We don't knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. The app doesn't require any personal information to function.
			</p>

			<h2>Your Rights</h2>
			<p>
				You have control over your data:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Delete the app at any time to remove all local data</li>
				<li>Disable analytics collection in your device settings</li>
				<li>Disable notifications in your device settings</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Data Security</h2>
			<p>
				We take appropriate measures to protect your information:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>All data transmission uses HTTPS encryption</li>
				<li>Local data is protected by iOS device security</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
			<p>
				We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by updating the "Last updated" date at the top of this policy.
			</p>

			<h2>Contact</h2>
			<p>
				If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how BibleWise handles data, please contact us through the App Store where you downloaded the app.
			</p>

			<div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg">
				<p class="text-sm text-center text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
					<a href="/" class="hover:text-orange-600 transition-colors">&larr; Back to tskulbru.dev</a> |
					<a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/dev/stdeula/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="hover:text-orange-600 transition-colors">Terms of Use (EULA)</a>
				</p>
			</div>
		</article>
	</Section>
</Base>
